---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

// Last updated — bump this whenever the policy text changes.
const updated = "27 June 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Privacy — nag."
  description="nag keeps your habits on your device. No account, no cloud, no tracking. The only data that leaves your phone is anonymous diagnostics (crash, performance, and technical logs)."
>
  <!-- ──────── Page header ──────── -->
  <section class="section-sm section-pt-lg">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="kicker">Privacy</div>
      <h1 class="h-display" style="margin-top: 18px;">
        your habits stay<br />
        on your phone<span class="dot">.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lede" style="margin-top: 28px;">
        nag is built to keep your data on your device. There is no account, no
        cloud sync, and nothing to sell. The only thing that ever leaves your
        phone is anonymous diagnostics — crash reports plus some performance and
        technical logs — and this page explains exactly what that is.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ──────── Policy body ──────── -->
  <section class="section-pt-0" style="padding-bottom: 96px;">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="prose">
        <p><em>Last updated: {updated}</em></p>

        <h2>The short version</h2>
        <p>
          Your habits, check-ins, schedules, and reminders are stored only on
          your iPhone. nag does not have an account system, does not upload your
          data to a server, and does not track you across apps or websites. We
          collect no personal information. The single exception is anonymous
          diagnostics — crash, performance, and technical logs, described below
          — which contain no personal data and no information about your habits.
        </p>

        <h2>Data stored on your device</h2>
        <p>
          Everything you create in nag — your habits, their cadence and reminder
          times, your check-ins and skips, and any habits you archive — is saved
          in a private database on your device. This data is not transmitted to
          us or to anyone else. We never see it.
        </p>
        <p>
          Because this data lives only on your device, deleting the app removes
          it. We have no copy to delete on your behalf, and we cannot recover it
          for you.
        </p>

        <h2>Diagnostics we do collect</h2>
        <p>
          nag uses <a href="https://sentry.io/" rel="noopener">Sentry</a> to monitor
          the app's stability and performance. Some of this is sent during normal
          use — not only when something goes wrong:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Performance and technical logs.</strong> A sampled portion of
            timing data (how long screens and operations take) and technical operational
            logs (for example, "a sync run completed" or "a screen opened"), used
            to spot slowdowns and bugs.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Crash and error reports.</strong> When the app crashes or hits
            an error: the error type and a technical stack trace, plus a short replay
            of the moments before it — with all on-screen text and images masked —
            to help reproduce the problem.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Basic device info.</strong> Your device model, operating-system
            version, and the nag app version, attached to the above.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This data is used solely to keep the app stable and fast. It does not
          contain your habits, check-ins, notes, or any personal information,
          and we do not use it to identify you or to track you across other apps
          or services. Sentry processes this data on our behalf; see Sentry's
          own privacy documentation for how they handle it.
        </p>

        <h2>Notifications</h2>
        <p>
          nag's reminders are <strong>local notifications</strong> scheduled on your
          device. If you grant notification permission, your reminders are created
          and delivered entirely on your phone. nag does not use remote push notifications
          and does not send any device token or notification data to a server.
        </p>

        <h2>What nag does not do</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>No accounts, logins, or profiles.</li>
          <li>No advertising and no advertising identifiers.</li>
          <li>
            No product analytics, behavioural profiling, or cross-app tracking.
            (The diagnostics above are technical only — stability and
            performance.)
          </li>
          <li>
            No selling or sharing of your data — there is nothing to sell.
          </li>
          <li>
            No access to your location, contacts, photos, microphone, or camera.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>
          nag is not directed at children under 13 and does not knowingly
          collect personal information from anyone. Since the app collects no
          personal information, this is true for users of every age.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          If this policy changes, we will update the date at the top of this
          page. Material changes will be reflected here before they take effect.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about privacy in nag? Email <a
            href="mailto:privacy@auctionready.co.nz"
            >privacy@auctionready.co.nz</a
          >.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
